  "name": "Crocodile Aspect",
  "permission": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "feat",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>The crocodile lurks in the water, unseen until it lunges forth with its powerful jaws.</em><br><br><strong>Minor Form:</strong> You gain a +2 competence bonus on Swim checks and grapple combat maneuver checks.</p>\n<p>This bonus increases to +4 at 8th level and +6 at 15th level.<br><br><strong>Major Form: </strong>Your shape changes to that of a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.aonprd.com/MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Crocodile\">crocodile</a>. While in this form, you gain a swim speed of 30 feet, low-light vision, a bite attack (1d8) with the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.aonprd.com/UMR.aspx?ItemName=Grab\">grab</a>&nbsp;ability, and a tail slap attack (a secondary natural attack that deals 1d12 points of damage).</p>\n<p>At 8th level, once per minute as a free action, you can increase your land speed by 20 feet for 1 round.</p>\n<p>At 15th level, you gain&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.aonprd.com/FeatDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Improved%20Natural%20Attack\">Improved Natural Attack</a>&nbsp;with your bite attack, and when you successfully grapple a foe, you can knock your grappled foe prone.<br><br><strong>Alternate Natural Attacks:</strong> Bite (B, P, S), tail slap (B)</p>",
